= Chrono Trigger - Dual and Triple Techs =

This page documents all combination techs in Chrono Trigger, including the character combinations, MP costs, and damage formulas.

== Overview ==

Dual Techs combine the abilities of two characters, while Triple Techs use all three party members. Most combination techs deal more damage than the sum of their component techs.

== Dual Tech Data Structure ==

Each dual tech entry uses 16 bytes in ROM:

{| class="wikitable"
|-
! Offset !! Size !! Description
|-
| $00 || 1 || Character 1 ID
|-
| $01 || 1 || Character 2 ID
|-
| $02 || 1 || Tech 1 ID requirement
|-
| $03 || 1 || Tech 2 ID requirement
|-
| $04-$05 || 2 || Base power
|-
| $06 || 1 || Element type
|-
| $07 || 1 || Target type
|-
| $08-$09 || 2 || MP cost character 1
|-
| $0A-$0B || 2 || MP cost character 2
|-
| $0C-$0F || 4 || Animation data
|}

